WEBVTT

00:08:25.841 --> 00:08:30.379
And it says: "Alex just matched
five rhyming words.

00:08:30.403 --> 00:08:32.246
Ask him to play this game with you.

00:08:32.270 --> 00:08:35.094
Can you think of a word
that rhymes with 'cat'?

00:08:35.943 --> 00:08:37.534
Or how about 'ball'?"

00:08:38.797 --> 00:08:42.524
In our studies, when parents receive
simple tips like these,

00:08:42.548 --> 00:08:44.193
they felt empowered.

00:08:44.217 --> 00:08:45.827
They were so excited

00:08:45.851 --> 00:08:48.475
to play these games
at the dinner table with their kids.

00:08:48.499 --> 00:08:50.101
And the kids loved it, too.

00:08:50.125 --> 00:08:53.040
Not only did it feel like magic
that their parents knew

00:08:53.064 --> 00:08:54.627
what they had been playing,

00:08:54.651 --> 00:08:57.946
kids love to play games
with their parents.

00:08:59.176 --> 00:09:03.107
Just the act of talking to kids
about their media